// Project Registry
// Persists the list of registered projects to ~/.mermaid-collab/projects.json.

A singleton instance (projectRegistry) is exported for convenience.
Stale projects (paths that no longer exist) are automatically removed on list().

FUNCTION constructor(registryPath)
  Accept an optional registry path; defaults to ~/.mermaid-collab/projects.json.

---

FUNCTION load() -> ProjectRegistryData
  IF file does not exist, return empty { projects: [] }.
  Read and parse the JSON. IF structure is invalid, warn and return empty.

---

FUNCTION save(registry) -> void
  Create the parent directory if needed. Write JSON with formatting and a trailing newline.

---

FUNCTION register(path) -> { created }                                                  EXPORT (via instance)
  Throw if path is not absolute or does not exist on the filesystem.
  Load registry. IF project already exists, update lastAccess and return { created: false }.
  ELSE add new entry with name (basename of path) and current timestamp, return { created: true }.

---

FUNCTION list() -> Project[]                                                            EXPORT (via instance)
  Load registry. Validate each project path exists.
  Auto-remove stale entries and save (if any were stale).
  Return valid projects sorted by lastAccess descending.

---

FUNCTION unregister(path) -> boolean                                                    EXPORT (via instance)
  Load registry, filter out the entry matching path, save if changed.
  Return true if removed, false if not found.

---

FUNCTION touch(path) -> void                                                            EXPORT (via instance)
  Load registry, update lastAccess for the matching project, save.
  No-op if path is not registered.
